I was asked to give a talk-- and
it was quite an honor for me--

00:40:03.150 --> 00:40:04.850
to my medical school.

00:40:04.850 --> 00:40:07.470
Because, believe it or not,
my medical school actually

00:40:07.470 --> 00:40:10.680
let me into medical
school without a degree

00:40:10.680 --> 00:40:14.955
and with a GPA of
2.53 out of four.

00:40:18.630 --> 00:40:19.630
And that's a long story.

00:40:19.630 --> 00:40:22.800
It's in the book,
so read the book.

00:40:22.800 --> 00:40:28.580
But I ultimately-- at
the end of the day--

00:40:28.580 --> 00:40:31.170
I was the last person
who probably would

00:40:31.170 --> 00:40:32.560
be accepted to medical school.

00:40:32.560 --> 00:40:34.330
And in fact, I was
just with the president

00:40:34.330 --> 00:40:37.450
of the university and the
dean, and they told me

00:40:37.450 --> 00:40:39.220
I still have the record
for the lowest GPA

00:40:39.220 --> 00:40:40.261
and not getting a degree.

00:40:40.261 --> 00:40:42.790
So it's necessarily
I'm something proud of,

00:40:42.790 --> 00:40:45.220
but I had a few
distractors in there.

00:40:45.220 --> 00:40:49.130
But I want to talk
about this-- what I

00:40:49.130 --> 00:40:51.000
call the alphabet of the heart.

00:40:51.000 --> 00:40:52.770
And I'll tell you the story
about the medical school really

00:40:52.770 --> 00:40:53.270
quick.

00:40:53.270 --> 00:40:57.170
So they did accept me, and it
is a very unusual situation.

00:40:57.170 --> 00:41:00.605
But what happened is-- and
this is also to show you--

00:41:00.605 --> 00:41:05.060
you can never predict the
trajectory of someone's life.

00:41:05.060 --> 00:41:07.110
I became a very
successful entrepreneur

00:41:07.110 --> 00:41:08.230
as I indicated to you.

00:41:08.230 --> 00:41:14.340
After Hurricane Katrina, the
medical school was flooded.

00:41:14.340 --> 00:41:16.800
They moved the medical
school to Baylor in Houston.

00:41:16.800 --> 00:41:19.730
The present dean-- he got
so depressed about this,

00:41:19.730 --> 00:41:20.290
he resigned.

00:41:20.290 --> 00:41:21.480
They had no dean.

00:41:21.480 --> 00:41:26.230
The library was damaged.

00:41:26.230 --> 00:41:28.500
So they were trying
to recruit a dean,

00:41:28.500 --> 00:41:30.610
and they wanted a
fellow from Harvard.

00:41:30.610 --> 00:41:32.550
But he wanted an endowed chair.

00:41:32.550 --> 00:41:36.810
Well, I was in the
position to endow his chair

00:41:36.810 --> 00:41:38.340
and repair the library.

00:41:38.340 --> 00:41:41.220
And I set up a multimillion
dollar scholarship for students

00:41:41.220 --> 00:41:43.430
who were going into service.

00:41:43.430 --> 00:41:47.550
Yet, I was the last person
who you would probably

00:41:47.550 --> 00:41:50.929
think would be accepted
to medical school.

00:41:50.929 --> 00:41:52.470
And so I'm on the
Board of Governors,

00:41:52.470 --> 00:41:54.636
the President's Council of
the university, the board

00:41:54.636 --> 00:41:56.960
of administrators, et cetera.

00:41:56.960 --> 00:42:00.560
My point is that you
can do amazing things,

00:42:00.560 --> 00:42:03.220
and you can never
predict the power

00:42:03.220 --> 00:42:06.620
you have over another
person to change

00:42:06.620 --> 00:42:09.800
their life like this
Ruth person did for me.

00:42:09.800 --> 00:42:11.660
And each of us-- no
matter our position--

00:42:11.660 --> 00:42:14.410
if you recognize another
person and give them

00:42:14.410 --> 00:42:16.740
the gift of your
time or attention,

00:42:16.740 --> 00:42:18.076
you can change everything.

00:42:18.076 --> 00:42:19.951
But back to these 10
letters of the alphabet.

00:42:22.600 --> 00:42:27.570
So I was asked to give this
talk to the new medical students

00:42:27.570 --> 00:42:30.280
to try to inspire them
for a future in medicine.

00:42:30.280 --> 00:42:32.890
And I spent a lot of time
thinking about this, including

00:42:32.890 --> 00:42:37.760
my time with Ruth and all the
lessons that I had learned

00:42:37.760 --> 00:42:39.360
and all the science behind it.

00:42:39.360 --> 00:42:41.930
And I came up with 10
letters of the alphabet

00:42:41.930 --> 00:42:46.530
that I actually now use as
my own personal practice.

00:42:46.530 --> 00:42:49.570
And it starts with
C and ends with L.

00:42:49.570 --> 00:42:52.580
And I go through this with
intention multiple times a day,

00:42:52.580 --> 00:42:55.880
and it centers me and,
again, clarifies my intention

00:42:55.880 --> 00:42:57.960
as to who I wish to be.

00:42:57.960 --> 00:43:01.240
And that's compassion
for self and others.

00:43:01.240 --> 00:43:05.240
Recognizing the dignity
of every person.

00:43:05.240 --> 00:43:06.340
Practicing equanimity.

00:43:08.900 --> 00:43:11.105
Practicing forgiveness.

00:43:11.105 --> 00:43:12.480
Because what
happens with so many

00:43:12.480 --> 00:43:15.310
is you hold these
emotions, because you

00:43:15.310 --> 00:43:16.670
think someone has wronged you.

00:43:16.670 --> 00:43:19.060
And it stops you
from connecting.

00:43:19.060 --> 00:43:20.630
And you always carry this.

00:43:20.630 --> 00:43:22.150
So forgiveness.

00:43:22.150 --> 00:43:23.310
Having gratitude.

00:43:23.310 --> 00:43:25.830
Science has now shown that
showing gratitude-- having

00:43:25.830 --> 00:43:28.980
gratitude-- is
one of the biggest

00:43:28.980 --> 00:43:33.290
effectors of your own health
and mental well-being.

00:43:33.290 --> 00:43:35.660
You know, so many
people in this area--

00:43:35.660 --> 00:43:38.390
they're always looking up
about what others have.

00:43:38.390 --> 00:43:42.420
Yet if you look down and you see
what the rest of the world has,

00:43:42.420 --> 00:43:45.980
you're one of the most
blessed people in the world.

00:43:45.980 --> 00:43:46.782
H is humility.

00:43:46.782 --> 00:43:48.240
I will tell you,
as a neurosurgeon,

00:43:48.240 --> 00:43:51.990
practicing humility is
probably the hardest.

00:43:51.990 --> 00:43:52.900
Nobody says anything.

00:43:52.900 --> 00:43:53.840
You're supposed to laugh.

00:43:53.840 --> 00:43:55.420
Neurosurgeons are
not usually humble.

00:43:57.990 --> 00:44:00.630
It's difficult,
but, you know, when

00:44:00.630 --> 00:44:03.330
you recognize-- it's hard to
be compassionate to another

00:44:03.330 --> 00:44:05.560
person, to care
for another person,

00:44:05.560 --> 00:44:07.520
if you're looking down on them.

00:44:07.520 --> 00:44:12.250
These practices have
to be done eye to eye.

00:44:12.250 --> 00:44:14.690
Because no one is
better than you,

00:44:14.690 --> 00:44:17.160
and you're better than no one.

00:44:17.160 --> 00:44:20.260
The other one is integrity
or having personal values

00:44:20.260 --> 00:44:22.910
that you live by.

00:44:22.910 --> 00:44:27.500
Then one that is important
to me is justice.

00:44:27.500 --> 00:44:31.177
We have a responsibility
for our privileged position

00:44:31.177 --> 00:44:32.926
to care for those who
are most vulnerable.

00:44:35.950 --> 00:44:38.600
The last is the active
component of compassion,

00:44:38.600 --> 00:44:41.580
which is kindness.

00:44:41.580 --> 00:44:44.930
And all of this is
contained by love.

00:44:47.530 --> 00:44:49.655
Those are the 10 letters now.

00:44:49.655 --> 00:44:51.780
I'll end this with telling
you an interesting story

00:44:51.780 --> 00:44:53.050
about those 10 letters.

00:44:53.050 --> 00:44:56.424
About two months after I
got-- or I gave-- that talk,

00:44:56.424 --> 00:44:57.590
I got an email from a woman.

00:44:57.590 --> 00:44:59.089
She said, I'm the
spiritual director

00:44:59.089 --> 00:45:02.310
of the largest homeless
shelter in the United States.

00:45:02.310 --> 00:45:06.299
And she said, all my
friends had sent me

00:45:06.299 --> 00:45:07.590
notes because I was burned out.

00:45:07.590 --> 00:45:08.880
I couldn't go to work anymore.

00:45:08.880 --> 00:45:10.170
I had resigned my position.

00:45:10.170 --> 00:45:14.310
And on my last day at work
after everything had failed,

00:45:14.310 --> 00:45:16.530
I saw your talk that
goes through these 10

00:45:16.530 --> 00:45:17.822
letters of the alphabet.

00:45:17.822 --> 00:45:19.530
And it was so inspiring
to me, it gave me

00:45:19.530 --> 00:45:20.821
the strength to return to work.

00:45:20.821 --> 00:45:24.660
And I was, of course,
incredibly moved by that.

00:45:24.660 --> 00:45:26.240
And so I thanked
her for the note.

00:45:26.240 --> 00:45:28.031
And a few months later,
she said, you know,

00:45:28.031 --> 00:45:29.942
we started using
this on our clients.

00:45:29.942 --> 00:45:30.900
And it's very powerful.

00:45:30.900 --> 00:45:33.760
We use it every morning
to start our day.

00:45:33.760 --> 00:45:35.315
And again, I'm
extraordinarily moved.

00:45:35.315 --> 00:45:37.070
She sent me another note.

00:45:37.070 --> 00:45:42.860
And she says, you know, my best
friend's daughter makes beads.

00:45:42.860 --> 00:45:46.300
And she says, as you know,
in all religions beads

00:45:46.300 --> 00:45:48.110
are utilized for centering.

00:45:48.110 --> 00:45:51.740
She said, my friend's
daughter made a set of beads

00:45:51.740 --> 00:45:54.270
with 10 wooden
beads, but she also

00:45:54.270 --> 00:46:00.370
added another bead, which was
to represent the golden rule.

00:46:00.370 --> 00:46:04.100
And she said, I've started using
this and carrying this around.

00:46:04.100 --> 00:46:07.430
And would you mind if we
sell this as a fundraiser?

00:46:07.430 --> 00:46:08.550
So then they did that.

00:46:08.550 --> 00:46:09.630
Then a few months passed.

00:46:09.630 --> 00:46:11.280
She sends me another email.

00:46:11.280 --> 00:46:14.050
And she says, we made a
video about these beads,

00:46:14.050 --> 00:46:15.710
because they're so powerful.

00:46:15.710 --> 00:46:16.630
And it's on YouTube.

00:46:16.630 --> 00:46:17.910
And it's called
compassion beads,

00:46:17.910 --> 00:46:19.493
and it's associated
also with her work

00:46:19.493 --> 00:46:21.480
at the San Antonio Peace Center.

00:46:21.480 --> 00:46:24.780
And it's this
beautiful video that

00:46:24.780 --> 00:46:28.350
talks about how utilizing
these in practices.

00:46:28.350 --> 00:46:30.160
And this is clarity
of intention.

00:46:30.160 --> 00:46:34.330
It creates, if you will,
these compassion super-neural

00:46:34.330 --> 00:46:35.580
highways.

00:46:35.580 --> 00:46:38.380
And so this has gone
on, and now these

00:46:38.380 --> 00:46:39.820
are sold all over the world.

00:46:39.820 --> 00:46:42.222
But it's really a
powerful statement.

00:46:42.222 --> 00:46:43.930
And I actually carry
them around with me,

00:46:43.930 --> 00:46:46.010
and it's become actually
my own practice.

00:46:46.010 --> 00:46:48.560
Because at any time, I can
just touch one of those

00:46:48.560 --> 00:46:54.010
and it puts me into this mode
of self-reflection, connection,

00:46:54.010 --> 00:46:58.610
and sort of trying or
aspiring to be the best

00:46:58.610 --> 00:46:59.750
person that I can be.

00:46:59.750 --> 00:47:01.500
And I know that's
what all of us want.

00:47:01.500 --> 00:47:02.545
So thank you.

